  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries and add them to a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Strip your <strong>rosemary leaves</strong> off their stems, then chop them as finely as possible and discard the stems</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped rosemary</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – this is your<strong> rosemary salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Sprinkle the <strong>rosemary salt</strong> over the fries with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> and mix it all together</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until crisp, golden and cooked through – these are your <strong>rosemary salted fries</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the fries are cooking, add your <strong>beef mince</strong> to a bowl with your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong>, mix it all together (clean hands is the best way!), then shape into 1 burger patty per person</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a light covering of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> to a separate baking tray (use kitchen paper<strong> </strong>to spread it evenly!), then add the <strong>burger patty[ies] </strong>and your <strong>smoked streaky bacon</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? Use 2 trays!</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 15-20 min or until the burger[s] is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the bacon is crispy</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-4-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-4-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-4-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-4-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-4-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the burger[s] is cooking, combine your <strong>mustard ketchup</strong>, <strong>mayo</strong> and <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>ketchup</strong> in a bowl – this is your <strong>burger sauce</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Slice your <strong>brioche bun[s]</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-5-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-5-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-5-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-5-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-5-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong> and pat dry with kitchen paper, then remove 1 <strong>whole outer leaf</strong> per person and set aside for serving</p><p>Chop the <strong>remaining lettuce</strong> into quarters, then add to a bowl and toss with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and season lightly with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – these are your <strong>dressed lettuce wedges</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1619432547605-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1619432547605-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1619432547605-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1619432547605-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-copy-1619432547605-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the burger[s] is almost done, top the patty with the <strong>grated cheese</strong> and return the tray to the oven for 3 min or until the cheese has melted – this is your <strong>cheeseburger patty</strong></p><p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat and add the <strong>brioche bun halves</strong>, cut side down, and cook for 3 min or until toasted and charred</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 3 or more? You may need to do this in 2 batches!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-7-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-7-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-7-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-7-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2120.-step-7-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To build, spread a little <strong>burger sauce</strong> onto the <strong>toasted brioche base</strong>, then pile up with a <strong>lettuce leaf</strong>, a <strong>cheeseburger patty</strong>, <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>bacon </strong>and top with the <strong>toasted brioche lid</strong> – this is your <strong>ultimate bacon cheeseburger</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>ultimate bacon cheeseburger</strong> with the <strong>rosemary salted fries</strong>, <strong>dressed lettuce wedges </strong>and any <strong>remaining burger sauce</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
